# PRism Review Rules
# ==================
# Rules in this file are injected into every AI review pass as mandatory instructions.
# The AI will follow these rules strictly and they override its default behavior.
#
# Write rules as plain statements — one per line.
# Lines starting with # are comments and are ignored by the reviewer.
# Blank lines are ignored.
#
# Examples:
#   Never flag console.log usage in test files.
#   We use camelCase for variables and PascalCase for types — do not flag this as inconsistent.
#   All API endpoints must validate input with Zod — flag any that don't.
#   Ignore minor naming suggestions — only flag names that are actively misleading.
#
# You can also set global rules (applied across all repos) via the
# PRISM_GLOBAL_RULES environment variable in your .env file.
